args: If you're awake, show yourself already!
What need have you two of me?
We want you to join our family!
...I see. You are all pretending to be\npart of Tiki's extended family.
No ＂pretending＂ here—we ARE family!\nAnd it has nothing to do with blood or\nother relations—it's a matter of the heart.
And what would you have me do?
Um, well, Mym is my big sister,\nand Zod-Zod is my grandpa...
Mercury is my mother and Jupiter is\nmy little brother, soooo...how about\nyou be my father?!
I guess you can be another little brother\nif you like the sound of that better?
No, it's not that. I simply wondered if it\nmight not be more suitable for Zodiark\nto assume the position of father.
I told you, he's my grandpa!
Yes, of course. How foolish of me...
Come on, FATHER! It suits you!\nYou've got that cock-of-the-walk\nthing going on, after all!
Does that serve as a reason?
It sure as heck DOES! Right, Tiki?
Yeah! Don't you like it, Father?
Heh. I suppose one never knows what\nwill happen when you live a long time.
Right? You can even end up\nwith a whole new family!
I've lived a long time, so it's always really\nlonely when I have to say goodbye to\nmy friends and...and...
Oh my gosh. I'm going to leave this world.\nI'll have to say goodbye to all of you.
Speaking of saying goodbye...\nYou've certainly changed, Brunhilda.
I never thought of you as one who would\nembrace the title of an elder sister.
Why does everyone find this so weird?!

I mean no offense. You have simply never
been fond of partings, and yet you are
assuming a large role in the life of one
who will soon abandon this world.
I've made progress in that area\nsince I met my darling!
I'm not going to be worried\nand hesitant forever!
Very well. I will go along with this plan.\nBut if you are to be sisters, I insist that\nyou fulfill your duties to the very end!
Aren't you embarrassed to be fighting in\nfront of your child?!
Tiki, where did you hear something\nlike that?
Mother Mercury said it,\nand I think she's right!
Heh... Ha! AAAAH HA HA HA HA!
Okay, you were grumpy a second ago,\nso why are you laughing?
Heh heh... Goodness me. I've simply\nnever been scolded in such a fashion.

You truly have the spirit of a princess.
And as an apology for showing you such
an unsightly side of myself, I shall grant
you a magnificent boon.
I have oft heard that it is a father's duty\nto indulge his children, so—
That's where you pick me up and put me\non your shoulders! All the fathers do it.
So if you're granting fine boons and stuff,\nI want a horsey ride.
Very well. I will keep my promise.\nYou may ride my shoulders.
Yaaaay! Thank you, Father!\nYou ride up here too, Big Sis!
Yeah! It'll be a sign that the\ntwo of you have made up.
Then shove over, 'cause I'm gettin' on!
Oh, I'm serious as an anvil, buddy.
Hee hee! Now THIS is the way we\nshould all be getting along!
Still, I wonder how much longer\nI'll be able to be with everyone...
Right then! Where should we have\nour dear old father take us?
I realize I promised to fulfill this absurd\nrequest, but let us at least attempt to\nkeep it at a reasonable distance.
Still, I suppose this ＂father＂ thing\nis not altogether unpleasant...
